Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay near fine buff-brown; grey core; some mica. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Almost certainly the same piece as drawn by Petrie, Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) 102, 9.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1659)
